Unisa offered an 8% pay hike for the lowest category worker and 6.5% for employees at the upper end of the wage scale. JOHANNESBURG - Trade union Nehawu says its members have rejected the latest wage offer from the University of South Africa (Unisa).In the proposal, Unisa offered an 8% pay hike for the lowest category worker and 6.5% for employees at the upper end of the wage scale.But workers have rejected the deal, demanding an across the board 8% increase.Nehawu s Khaya Xaba says the strike continues and workers will again block the entrances at Unisa campuses. Unless management is willing to make one offer that will cover everyone, workers are not going to accept that and the strike will continue. 